;B[ps]LB[os:1][ns:2][ps:3]C[Dia. 04 Value of Reverse Sente

{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}

Let's check Black's hane and connection with 1 and 3.
It was said that Black's hane and connection is gote, wasn't it?
Therefore Black 1 and 3 is \cf1\b 3 points gote endgame\cf0\b0 .

This gote endgame which provides the opponent to play sente endgame is on a different level from the simple gote endgame. This kind of endgame is called \cf1\b reverse sente\cf0\b0 .

The value of reverse sente is double. Therefore Black 1 and 3 is not 3, but 6 points.

